Firiona Vie Server (Roleplaying)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujantisconstanceeorle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jantis ConstanceEorle</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/9/01 10:55:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=20>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.warghoul.com/images/CoSS/jantis_head_ez.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_devil.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: How much do you want Verant to coddle this server?</span><hr size=1> A few problems.  Are you asking what I want, or what I expect?<br>
<br>
Verant has shown they have no means or desire to police anything.  The guide teams do a great job 90% of the time, but they are restricted by the 'player police' attitude that Verant has adopted.  So if you are expecting actual enforcement of roleplaying, I think you're pushing it.  For me personally, it would be wonderful.  <br>
<br>
They didn't create the 'Alternate Ruleset' server, they created the 'Roleplaying Preferred' server.  So if you are here to play with the alternate ruleset, but you are using /auction as your /ooc, then you aren't cooperating with the server designs.  Instead you are doing what far too many people have done in EverQuest and just playing by the rules you like and giving the old /rude to the rules you don't.  Why do you do this?  Because Verant has shown you it's like breaking the rules in high school... it's only bad if you get caught.  That stinks in my opinion.  If you want an 'Alternate Ruleset' server, then complain about it to Verant.  They have shown that one of the few things they do tend to listen to complaint-wise is when people demand a server.  Of course, they may take a year or two to actually come out with it, but...<br>
<br>
On the other hand, those of you that expect the Roleplay Police don't quite get the server name either.  It is 'Roleplay Preferred', not 'Roleplay Enforced'.  Why did they do this?  It goes back to my original point that Verant either does not have the means (ie, they won't fork over the dough for people to be hired to do so) or the desire (they have the dough but Brad needs a new Porsche) to hire enough people to do what Dark Age is attempting.  Will the RP servers in Dark Age work?  I don't know, you don't know... but time will tell.  However, Mythic gets an &quot;A&quot; for effort in at least trying it, and trying it correctly.<br>
<br>
The Firiona Vie server is the half-arsed RP server.  The original post hits one thing on the head... the server is what the players make of it.  Unfortunately, that is what every EQ server has been and most of them turn out about the same as the rest. There is a lot of hope for this server but it isn't all from &quot;Roleplayers, don't petition me for not saying 'Thou'&quot;.<br>
<br>
What I ask of those that don't want to roleplay, don't infringe on my desire to roleplay.  If you want to get in a group (or a guild if they ever get here) and chat about the Hockey Playoffs or the latest bombingings in Afghanistan... feel free.  But don't use /auction to do it or yes, I will use /report.  If I'm on a CR and I run by someone that says &quot;1697 Mustang&quot;, I'm not going to report or petition you.  But if I'm talking to my sweet darling and telling her of my anger over the invading orcs and you feel the need to say &quot;u rprz suxxorz&quot;, then yes, I will /report /petition you.  If you're going to be a grief player, ot nor play within the confines of the new ruleset (ie, no /ooc), then I will be glad to get you booted off the server if I can.  You can't just play by the rules you like and whine and cry when you get in trouble for breaking the other rules.  Tonight I reported some jerk for making Afghanistan jokes in /auction.  <br>
<br>
By the way, I think the folks that cannot speak in terms beyond &quot;Oh, thou fine lady of the angelic breathe, how thy heart doth make my soul bleed in tiny puddles at thy feet&quot; are cheeseballs (though I must say, most of them aren't even as creative as that example just was).  Yes, there are components to dialect and languages, even from the great bard himself, that make for wonderful roleplaying components.  But if it looks fake, then it is fake.  Learn context and atmosphere or maybe you would be better suited to roleplay a mime.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#A62A2A>- </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie>Firiona Vie</a><font color=#A62A2A> - </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4>The Soapbox</a> <font color=#A62A2A> - </font><a href="http://www.firionavie.org/">Firiona Vie</a><font color=#A62A2A> - </font> <center><a href="http://www.firiona-vie.com/fvchat.html" target="_blank"><h3>Chat Room</a></h3></center> <br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.6.2<br>Copyright ©1999-2001 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  